Create a tibble to hold data and models. Each row of the tibble will correspond to one time point. Each row has a subsetted dge that corresponds to that time point.

models <- tibble(day_time=unique(dge$samples$day_time))
models <- models %>%
    separate(day_time, into=c("day", "time"), sep="-", remove=FALSE) %>%
  mutate(dge=map(day_time, ~ dge[,dge$samples$day_time==.]))

#Do NOT print the full models tibble to the screen, it slows everything way down!!
#models

models %>% select(-dge) #%>% View()

“2-afternoon” data. y ~ trt + day + trt:day

# subset data
dge.twoafternoon<-dge[,dge$samples$sampling_time=="2_afternoon"]
# reset normalization factor
dge.twoafternoon$samples$norm.factors<-1 # # No matter which case, non-normalize libraries.
# filtering
dge.twoafternoon<-dge.twoafternoon[rowSums(cpm(dge.twoafternoon)>1) >=3,keep.lib.sizes=FALSE]
# #relevel soil_trt to "SBC_OLD" 
dge.twoafternoon$samples<-dge.twoafternoon$samples %>% mutate(soil_trt=fct_relevel(soil_trt,"ATM_BLANK")) # %>% str() 
## model
dge.twoafternoon.design <- with(dge.twoafternoon$samples, model.matrix(~ soil_trt + sampling_day + soil_trt:sampling_day + block))
# estimateDisp
dge.twoafternoon <- estimateDisp(dge.twoafternoon,design = dge.twoafternoon.design)
## fit linear model
dge.twoafternoon.fit<- glmFit(dge.twoafternoon,dge.twoafternoon.design)
# get DEGs, soil_trt effects (coef=c("SBC_OLD"))
twoafternoon.trtlive.lrt <- glmLRT(dge.twoafternoon.fit,coef = c("soil_trtSBC_OLD"))
## all
twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs.all <- topTags(twoafternoon.trtlive.lrt,n = Inf,p.value = 1)$table
## pvalue < 0.05
twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs <- topTags(twoafternoon.trtlive.lrt,n = Inf,p.value = 0.05)$table;nrow(twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs) # 1474
## [1] 1474

diurnal data. One analysis for day 3+4 and a separate analysis for days 13+14

# subset data
dge.diurnal<-dge[,dge$samples$sampling_day %in% c("13","14")]
dge.diurnal$samples
# reset normalization factor
dge.diurnal$samples$norm.factors<-1 # # No matter which case, non-normalize libraries.
# filtering
dge.diurnal<-dge.diurnal[rowSums(cpm(dge.diurnal)>1) >=3,keep.lib.sizes=FALSE]
# relevel soil_trt to "SBC_OLD" 
dge.diurnal$samples<-dge.diurnal$samples %>% mutate(soil_trt=fct_relevel(soil_trt,"ATM_BLANK")) # %>% str() 
# relevel sampling_time to "1_morn"
dge.diurnal$samples<-dge.diurnal$samples %>% mutate(sampling_time=fct_relevel(sampling_time,"1_morn")) # %>% str() 
# model
dge.diurnal.design <- with(dge.diurnal$samples, model.matrix(~ soil_trt + sampling_time + soil_trt:sampling_time + block))
colnames(dge.diurnal.design)

# annotation file for v3.0annotation
Br.v3.0.At.BLAST <- read_csv(file.path("..","Annotation_copy","output","v3.0annotation","Brapa_v3.0_annotated.csv")) 
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X1' [1]
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),
##   name = col_character(),
##   chrom = col_character(),
##   subject = col_character(),
##   AGI = col_character(),
##   At_symbol = col_character(),
##   At_full_name = col_character(),
##   At_gene_model_type = col_character(),
##   At_short_description = col_character(),
##   At_Curator_summary = col_character(),
##   At_Computational_description = col_character()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
# This annotation is redundant with name (Br grene). Eg 
Br.v3.0.At.BLAST %>% filter(name=="BraA01g040570.3C")
# reduce the redundancy (112418)
Br.v3.0anno.At.BLAST.highscore <- Br.v3.0.At.BLAST %>% group_by(name) %>% arrange(desc(score)) %>% dplyr::slice(1)

# add annotiona with full name objects (all)
twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs.all.v3.0anno <- left_join(twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs.all %>% rownames_to_column(var="genes"),Br.v3.0anno.At.BLAST.highscore,by=c(genes="name")) %>%  dplyr::select(1:6, AGI, At_symbol, At_short_description, perc_ID)
twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs.all.v3.0anno
# write csv (all)
## trt
write.csv(twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs.all.v3.0anno,file=file.path("..","output","twoafternoon.trtlive.DEGs.all.v3.0anno.csv"))
